      "content": "It's a profound and ancient feeling, but the universe doesn't actually care about your suffering or your fleeting existence. The sheer scale of the cosmos makes your life feel insignificant, yet it's the only way to truly appreciate how fragile and precious it is. If we stop trying to find meaning, we might as well just let go, because the end is inevitable regardless of how hard we try.",
      "source": "target",
